post_text: Marfa ISD would like to inform you that on September 8, 2020, The Marfa City Council approved Gonzales Street to become a one way street heading north between Lincoln and Columbia and are putting up the signs today. This will help make the dropping off and picking up of students safer and more efficient. This will also allow us to practice social distancing during student drop off and pick up, because parents will be required to stay in their vehicles and students will not be walking across traffic.

post_text: Marfa ISD has been advised by our local health advisor, Dr. Schwartz, that there is a spike in cases of Covid-19 and recommends extending our remote only instruction for one more week. Due to this recommendation, Marfa ISD will be remote only for the week of September 14th through the 18th. Face to face instruction will begin, Monday, September 21, 2020 unless otherwise advised. Marfa ISD is sorry for any inconvenience this may cause you, but please understand that this decision is made with the safety of our students, staff, and community as the utmost priority.

post_text:
Nineteen years ago, on this day, the United States of America came under attack by terrorists. 2974 people died this 11th day of September at the World Trade Center, the Pentagon, and on 4 hi-jacked planes. On this 19th year anniversary of September 11, 2001, certainly many people feel that the events of that day must never be forgotten.
Today we remember and honor the thousands of people who died in the events of September 11, 2001. We recognize the endurance of those who survived, the courage of those who risked their lives to save others, and the compassion of all who supported one another. May the lives remembered, the deeds recognized, and the spirit reawakened be eternal beacons, which reaffirm respect for life, strengthen our resolve to preserve freedom, and inspire an end to hatred, ignorance and intolerance.
Let‚Äôs make sure that none of us take for granted our personal liberties and freedoms that have come through great sacrifice, past and present.

post_text:
Here are a few highlights from the July, 20, 2020 Marfa ISD school board meeting:

The first day of instruction will be Tuesday, September 8, 2020 and will be remote instruction only for the first week.

Marfa will start instruction remotely, then limited face to face instruction will begin September 14, 2020. More details will follow in the upcoming weeks.

All students, staff, and visitors will be required to wear masks or face shields.

Students that choose remote instruction will be allowed to participate in extracurricular activities if they adhere to requirements set by Marfa ISD. For example, students will be required to attend face to face practice daily.
text:
Here are a few highlights from the July, 20, 2020 Marfa ISD school board meeting:

The first day of instruction will be Tuesday, September 8, 2020 and will be remote instruction only for the first week.

Marfa will start instruction remotely, then limited face to face instruction will begin September 14, 2020. More details will follow in the upcoming weeks.

All students, staff, and visitors will be required to wear masks or face shields.

Students that choose remote instruction will be allowed to participate in extracurricular activities if they adhere to requirements set by Marfa ISD. For example, students will be required to attend face to face practice daily.

post_text:
Due to new guidance from the Texas Education Agency released July 7, 2020 at their 3:00 pm conference call, Marfa ISD will be able to offer the alternate day return to school option for only the first three weeks of school. We are required to provide every student face-to-face instruction every day that we are open after that time. Marfa ISD administration still wants to hear your concerns and thoughts to better prepare for this upcoming school year, so we look forward to seeing you at the courthouse lawn from 11 a.m.-2 p.m. and 5:30-7 p.m. on Thursday, July 9; Monday, July 13; and Wednesday, July 15. You are also welcome to call or stop by the school offices to visit with administrators.

Oscar N Aguero

Strength and Conditioning UPDATE

In order to maintain the highest health and safety standards for MISD students and staff, the first two weeks of the summer strength and conditioning program will be administered virtually via Zoom or other electronic methods.

Although we are all eager to get back on the field and on the court as soon as possible to prepare for the upcoming sports season, the safety of our students and community members will continue to be our number one priority.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Good advice from the CDC. Here is a list of reasonable precautions to prevent the spread of the illness:
‚Ä¢ Don‚Äôt shake hands
‚Ä¢ Wash your hands regularly
‚Ä¢ Limit movement within the community, especially avoiding crowded placed and maintaining 3 to 6 ft of distance between people (at least an arm‚Äôs length)
‚Ä¢ If you are moving around in the community, don‚Äôt congregate in large groups
‚Ä¢ For those MARFA ISD students who have traveled to areas with known COVID-19 cases ‚Äì both inside and outside of the country ‚Äì we ask that you self-quarantine and monitor for symptoms. Students who have traveled should plan to stay home for two weeks after arriving home. Please contact your campus principal by email to let them know.
‚Ä¢ If you suspect you have symptoms of COVID-19, call your health care provider for medical advice .
‚Ä¢ Keep your child at home if he/she feels ill, even if you think it is just a cold.
‚Ä¢ Do not leave the house if you are ill, except to access medical care

March 12, 2020

Dear parent or guardian,
As always, the health and safety of our students is Marfa ISD‚Äôs number one priority. It is crucial we take every possible precaution to keep them safe. So, out of an abundance of caution for our students and staff, Marfa ISD will be closed Friday, March 13, 2020. While there is no immediate danger, spring break will begin a day early. This extra day will provide our custodial and maintenance teams an extra day of cleaning and disinfecting of all classrooms, desk, and materials. Classes will resume on our regular schedule on Tuesday, March 24, 2020.

post_text: Marfa ISD is proud to announce that we have received the statewide accountability ratings for 2018-2019 school year. The Shorthorns achieved a rating of 87 which is up 8 points from last year. In addition, schools receive distinction if they are in the top 25 percent of their comparison group as determined by the Texas Education Agency. Of the seven possible distinction areas, Marfa ISD received FOUR DISTINCTIONS! Mr. Oscar Aguero, Superintendent of Schools, stated ‚ÄúEach and every student at Marfa makes a huge difference. Our teachers are invested in reaching every learner, every day. We are growing and improving every day and will continue to improve!‚Äù Congratulations to the staff and students of Marfa ISD.

Wednesday, June 12
12:30 AM - 3 PM
Marfa High School Auditorium (J.E Gregg Auditorium)
Casting Directors: Emma Rogers / Stephanie Huang
Contact: Emma Rogers / 503 724 6224

Come to casting as you are, we will take photos, a short video and take down your information.
IF cast you will be compensated.

Brief Description: We will be filming a commercial for the Kia Telluride featuring Texas born fashion designer Brandon Maxwell. We will filming for two days (June 27th & 28th). At the core of our commercial is the town of Marfa and the people that live here. We will be filming students and teachers of the local school and various shots of Marfa residents just being themselves. For the school scene will film Brandon walking through the campus while kids play and run around in the background. We‚Äôll also see a teacher and students in a classroom.

If you have any questions or would like to be considered but can‚Äôt make the casting call, please contact Emma at 503 724 6224.
